environment.model.locations

Class Location

  • java.lang.Object
    • environment.model.locations.Location
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Pump, ShoppingArea, Till

    public abstract class Location
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    This abstract class encapsulates the behaviour of a location in the Station. This should be extended with concrete subclasses.
    Version:
    24/04/2017
    Author:
    Joshua_Eddy

        protected int maxQueueSize
        This value holds the maximum number of units (size of RoadUsers) that this location can have at any given point. If this is initialised as 0 then the maximum size of the Location's queue is infinite.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Location

        public Location(java.lang.Class<? extends Location> nextLocation,
                int maxQueueSize)
        Constructs a new Location for use in the Station.
        Parameters:
        nextLocation - The Class of the type of the next Location that this will move the RoadUsers contained with in it too.
        maxQueueSize - The maximum number of units (size of RoadUsers) that this location can have at any given point. If this is initialised as 0 then the maximum size of the Locations queue is infinite.
        See Also:
        #processQueue(HashMap), RoadUser, Station

    • Method Detail

      • processQueue

        public abstract void processQueue(java.util.Map<RoadUser,Location> toMove)
        Perform a process on the queue at this location. This abstract method will be different for each location. This method will be called upon every tick of the simulation.
        Parameters:
        toMove - HashMap<RoadUser, Class<? extends Location>> that denotes the RoadUsers that the Station will move to the next Location. The Key of the HashMap is of type RoadUser as each road user to be moved should be unique. The value denotes the current Location of the RoadUser key assigned to it.
        See Also:
        RoadUser, HashMap, LinkedList

      • enter

        public void enter(RoadUser newRoadUser)
        Adds a RoadUser to this Location only if the new RoadUser is not null and there is enough space in the queue for it.
        Parameters:
        newRoadUser - RoadUser to be added.
        See Also:

      • canContain

        public boolean canContain(RoadUser roadUser)
        Checks if the parameter RoadUser can be placed into this Location based on the size of the RoadUser's vehicle.
        Parameters:
        roadUser - The RoadUser that will potentially be added to this Location.
        Returns:
        boolean of whether there is enough space for the parameter RoadUser to be added to this location. If the RoadUser is already in this Location returns false.
        See Also:
        Station, RoadUser

      • returnToQueue

      • cloneLocation

        protected Location cloneLocation(Location clone)
        Clones this Location's details onto the parameter Location. This method should be called by the subclasses of Location passing an new instance of them selves as a parameter. The Class<? extends Location>> nextLocation is assumed to be correct as it will be initialised in the constructor of the new instance of Location that is passed as a parameter.
        Returns:
        A Location identical to this Location.

      • compare

        public abstract boolean compare(Location location)
        Retrieves whether this is more optimal for a RoadUser to enter than a specified Location. This method compares these two Locations differently depending on the type of Location.

        Returns:
        boolean this is better that the specified Location.
